  "body": "This work package depends on work done to migrate add favourite to status-desktop and migrate mobile-favourites as a flag to saved addresses; see: https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/6546\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nImplement syncing of saved addresses in status-go`\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\n- [x] Sync existing saved addresses across accounts\r\n- [x] Trigger syncing every time a change is done to saved addresses\r\n- [x] ~~Add a `soft_delete` table to sync deletion across devices~~\r\n  - Tried this approach, not a simple task. In the best scenario, it requires syncronized IDs for all items. It seems worth it only if done for all the items. Another approach of having the sync ids be the addresses is not bringing enough benefits. Therefore I'm going with the approach recommended by colleagues to have a soft-delete flag and sync the timestamp part of the data and hide these from the API.",
